I don’t even have the words to express how hard it is to write this, but my best friend passed in his sleep last night. Wally was my very first friend in LA, the love of my life, and the best companion I could have ever wished for. For almost 12 years he filled my days with so much love, snuggles and laughter. I don’t think I would have made it through the last decade out here without him. I just can’t believe he will never again greet me at the door, perch on my shoulder, or beg to sit on my lap while I pee. Rest in peace tiny boy. You are so, so, so loved.
